On 30.9.1895 the part in Nottinghamshire was transferred to Yorkshire West Riding, so thereafter 
    Auckley was entirely 
    in Yorkshire West Riding,See also Table 2, note (d).
Abolished 9.11.1914 and added to the parish of Doncaster.

Created 1.10.1921 from the separate parishes of Barnby upon Don 
    and Kirk Sandall. See also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.10.1921 and added to the parish of Barnby Dun 
    with Kirk Sandall.
Abolished 1.4.1920 and added to the parish of Hooton Pagnell.
Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish of Dearne.
Abolished 1.4.1938 and added to the parish of Norton.
Abolished 9.11.1914 and added to the parish of Doncaster.

Created 1.4.1921 out of the parish of Conisbrough. See also Table 
    2, note (d).
Created 1.4.1937 out of the parishes of Bolton upon Dearne, Thurnscoe and Barnbrough. See also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Doncaster unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (e).

Abolished 1.10.1921 and added to the parish of Barnby Dun 
    with Kirk Sandall.

Abolished 25.3.1883 and divided between the parishes of Adwick 
   -le-Street and Thorpe in Balne.
Abolished 25.3.1886 and added to the parish of Kirk Sandall.

On 20.5.1886 the part in Lincolnshire was transferred to Nottinghamshire, so that thereafter Mission was 
    entirely in Nottinghamshire. 
    See also Table 2, note (c).
Abolished 1.4.1915 and added to the parish of Adwick-le-Street.

Created 1.10.1924 out of the parish of Stainton. See also Table 
    2, note (d).

Abolished 25.3.1886 and divided between the parishes of Wadworth 
    and Stainton.
Abolished 1.4.1920 and added to the parish of Hooton Pagnell.
Abolished 1.4.1938 and added to the parish of Norton.
Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish of Dearne.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Tickhill. Abolished 
    31.3.1896 and added to the parish of Tickhill.
Abolished 9.11.1914 and added to the parish of Doncaster.
